experiments.surfaceMcpToNewCloudUsers.on:
Set up the n8n MCP server for Cursor across all projects.

1. Open ~/.cursor/mcp.json (create the file and directory if they don't exist). Add the entry below, merging with any existing config so other servers stay intact:

   {'{'}
     "mcpServers": {'{'}
       "n8n": {'{'}
         "url": "{serverUrl}"
       {'}'}
     {'}'}
   {'}'}

2. Once it's saved, remind me to restart Cursor and complete the n8n OAuth flow when it prompts me — the server's tools won't be available until then.

